Even the messageSource bean exists in the parent context, it won't be recognized by Spring Web Flow.

The pre-existence of messageSource bean is checked at the below statement in registerMessageSource method of org.springframework.webflow.engine.builder.model.FlowModelFlowBuilder class.
{code:java}
	boolean localMessageSourcePresent
	= flowContext.containsLocalBean( AbstractApplicationContext.MESSAGE_SOURCE_BEAN_NAME);
{code}
That flowContext object is org.springframework.web.context.support.GenericWebApplicationContext type, and is instantiated by the statements below in createFlowApplicationContext method of org.springframework.webflow.engine.builder.model.FlowModelFlowBuilder:
{code:java}
	if (parent instanceof WebApplicationContext) {
		GenericWebApplicationContext webContext = new GenericWebApplicationContext();
		webContext.setServletContext(((WebApplicationContext) parent).getServletContext());
		flowContext = webContext;
	} else {
		flowContext = new GenericApplicationContext();
	}
{code}
Since it's using GenericWebApplicationContext constructor with no argument but one with DefaultListableBeanFactory argument, the newly instantiated DefaultListableBeanFactory object will be assigned to beanFactory member field (defined as final) of flowContext as you see below:
{code:java}
	public GenericApplicationContext() {
		this.beanFactory = new DefaultListableBeanFactory();
		this.beanFactory.setSerializationId(getId());
		this.beanFactory.setParameterNameDiscoverer(new LocalVariableTableParameterNameDiscoverer());
		this.beanFactory.setAutowireCandidateResolver(new QualifierAnnotationAutowireCandidateResolver());
	}
{code}
And the containsLocalBean method (what is used to check the messageSource bean existence as mentioned above) just delegates to the containsLocalBean method of this beanFactory member field like below:

	In org.springframework.context.support.AbstractApplicationContext class:
{code:java}
		public boolean containsLocalBean(String name) {
			return getBeanFactory().containsLocalBean(name);
		}
{code}

	In org.springframework.context.support.GenericApplicationContext class:
{code:java}
		@Override
		public final ConfigurableListableBeanFactory getBeanFactory() {
			return this.beanFactory;
		}
{code}

As you see that there isn't the pathway to negotiate the beanFactory in parent context here. 
Hence the messageSource bean will be newly instantiated ReloadableResourceBundleMessageSource object in registerMessageSource method of org.springframework.webflow.engine.builder.model.FlowModelFlowBuilder class like below.
(I kept all flow files including the message property files in each flow directory.)
{code:java}
	if (!localMessageSourcePresent) {
		Resource messageBundle;
		try {
			messageBundle = flowResource.createRelative("messages.properties");
		} catch (IOException e) {
			messageBundle = null;
		}
		if (messageBundle != null && messageBundle.exists()) {
			BeanDefinitionBuilder builder = BeanDefinitionBuilder
					.rootBeanDefinition(ReloadableResourceBundleMessageSource.class);
			builder.addPropertyValue("basename", "messages");
			if (isFlowInDevelopment()) {
				builder.addPropertyValue("cacheSeconds", "0");
			}
			flowContext.registerBeanDefinition(AbstractApplicationContext.MESSAGE_SOURCE_BEAN_NAME,
					builder.getBeanDefinition());
		}
	}
